<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B16FFBE6271FD0459C74011F802" author="Chamisso, L. K. A. &amp; Schlechtendal, F. L." box="[703,1147,1995,2022]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" pagination="570" refId="ref2274" refString="Chamisso, L. K. A. &amp; Schlechtendal, F. L. (1827) De plantis in expeditione speculatoria romanzoffiana observatis dissere pergunt: Scrophulariaceae. Linnaea 2 (4): 570." type="journal article" year="1827">Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendal (1827: 570)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D64FFBE6271FB4359C74114F802" authorityName="Bonati" authorityYear="1908" box="[1272,1406,1996,2022]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="godefroyi">
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBE6271FB4359C74114F802" box="[1272,1406,1996,2022]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">T. godefroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily differentiated from 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D64FFBE6271FE6A59FB4631F7ED" authorityName="Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendal" authorityYear="1827" box="[465,603,2032,2057]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Lindernia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crustacea">
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBE6271FE6A59FB4631F7ED" box="[465,603,2032,2057]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">T. crustacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its distinctly 5-winged calyx, enclosing the capsule completely (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B16FFBE6270FAE459FB4561FF5C" author="Prasad, M. G. &amp; Roy, P. K. &amp; Sunojkumar, P." lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="233" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" pagination="45 - 47" refId="ref2673" refString="Prasad, M. G., Roy, P. K. &amp; Sunojkumar, P. (2017) Re-establishment of the overlooked species Torenia godefroyi (Linderniaceae), and notes on the identity of T. lindernioides. Nordic Journal of Botany 35 (1): 45 - 47. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / njb. 01397" type="journal article" year="2017">
Prasad 
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBF6270FF335E9444D3FF5C" box="[136,185,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
., 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). During this study, the species was recorded from four localities, covering a stretch of 
<quantity id="4CCD9B02FFBF6270FB675E95415BFF5C" box="[1244,1329,158,184]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" unit="km" value="120.0">120 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C409BAFFFBF6270FA8A5E954153FF48" attach="left" box="[1329,1337,158,172]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">2</superScript>
area (
<figureCitation id="130E2A62FFBF6270FAC55E9544F2FF38" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1400,1422]" captionTargetBox="[160,1427,578,1366]" captionTargetId="figure-198@3.[151,1436,569,1375]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution map of Torenia godefroyi in Asia. Prepared by A. Pal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6622845" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6622845/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Several healthy populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D64FFBF6270FDA25EC846C8FF38" authorityName="Bonati" authorityYear="1908" box="[537,674,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Torenia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="godefroyi">
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBF6270FDA25EC846C8FF38" box="[537,674,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">T. godefroyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, even when 
<taxonomicName id="4C354D64FFBF6270FC835EC847AEFF38" authorityName="Chamisso &amp; Schlechtendal" authorityYear="1827" box="[824,964,195,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linderniaceae" genus="Lindernia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crustacea">
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBF6270FC835EC847AEFF38" box="[824,964,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">T. crustacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
started disappearing in early winter, were observed (except for some river beds, where both the species were present). We estimated the Extent of Occurrence of 
<quantity id="4CCD9B02FFBF6270FF1C5F014519FEC0" box="[167,371,266,293]" metricMagnitude="9" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9079235789999998" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" unit="km" value="3907923.579">3,907,923.579 km</quantity>
<superScript id="7C409BAFFFBF6270FEC85F014511FEFC" attach="left" box="[371,379,266,280]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">2</superScript>
using GeoCat (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B16FFBF6270FD915F01477FFEC0" author="Bachman, S. &amp; Moat, J. &amp; Hill, A. W. &amp; de la Torre, J. &amp; Scott, B." box="[554,789,266,293]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" pagination="117 - 126" refId="ref2173" refString="Bachman, S., Moat, J., Hill, A. W., de la Torre, J. &amp; Scott, B. (2011) Supporting Red List threat assessments with GeoCAT: geospatial conservation assessment tool. ZooKeys 150: 117 - 126. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 150.2109" type="journal article" year="2011">
Bachman 
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBF6270FD265F0046A4FEC0" box="[669,718,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
) which is much greater than 
<quantity id="4CCD9B02FFBF6270FBE15F0140B9FEC3" box="[1114,1235,266,295]" metricMagnitude="7" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" unit="km" value="20000.0">20,000 km</quantity>
² to be listed as any threatened category (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA44B16FFBF6270FEC85F254594FEAC" author="IUCN Standards &amp; Petitions Committee" box="[371,510,302,328]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" refId="ref2441" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee. (2019) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 18 April 2021)" type="book" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
). We also did not find any potential threat for the species as it shares different 
<typeStatus id="548E8845FFBF6270FACB5F2441C1FEAD" box="[1392,1451,303,329]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">types</typeStatus>
of habitats. So, we preliminary assess the IUCN status of this species as Least Concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F656CFFBF6270FF065F7D4131FE51" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8A36E7FFBF6270FF065F7D4131FE51" blockId="3.[136,1452,158,547]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B941EAF5FFBF6270FF065F7D4600FE74" bold="true" box="[189,618,374,400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Distribution, habitat and ecology:—</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F3227677FFBF6270FDD15F7D46CEFE74" box="[618,676,374,400]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">India</collectingCountry>
(Western Ghats and 
<collectingRegion id="49F1F805FFBF6270FC315F7C4071FE75" box="[906,1051,374,401]" country="India" name="West Bengal" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">West Bengal</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3227677FFBF6270FB965F7D40F9FE74" box="[1069,1171,374,400]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3227677FFBF6270FB255F7D417EFE74" box="[1182,1300,374,400]" name="Cambodia" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3227677FFBF6270FAA55F7D4117FE74" box="[1310,1405,374,400]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3227677FFBF6270FF335F9044A8FE51" box="[136,194,411,437]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="233">Laos</collectingCountry>
. Recently recorded from different habitats: bare marshy lands, sandy river beds, shaded forest edges, etc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32F656CFFBF6270FF065FB547FCFE3D" box="[189,918,446,473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="233" type="biology_ecology">
